history.content: You'll be fine for 61A. Phase II people shift around stuff and youll move up the list. Adjustment period, same thing. And during the first two weeks of class, I wouldn't be surprised if ~30-70 ppl dropped. IMO, You'll be enrolled in 61A by end of Phase II.

I am an Industrial Engineering + Operations Research major interested in completing an EECS minor with my degree. Given that, I intend to take EE16A and CS61A Fall 2018 (my sophomore year). As I do not come in the reserved seating for either of the two classes, what is the probability I get into:

A) EE16A given I am waitlist position 121.
B) CS61A given I am waitlist position 81.
